node_modules/
*.tsbuildinfo

# build/ is deliberately NOT ignored. It is produced by `pnpm run build` and
# consumed by go:embed in the explore package, which other repos import as a
# library — `go get` ships exactly what go:embed can see in the module, and
# nothing runs pnpm on the importer's side. So the built bundle is committed:
# re-run `make web` and commit build/ whenever src/ changes.
